20
00:00:48,569 --> 00:00:52,429
Wait... technically, it’s not a *Chinese*
military base.

21
00:00:52,429 --> 00:00:59,379
The pact simply gives China *exclusive rights*
to part of a *Cambodian* naval base.

22
00:00:59,379 --> 00:01:00,569
Still embarrassing, though.

23
00:01:00,569 --> 00:01:03,690
That’s why Cambodia’s prime minister is
doubling down,

24
00:01:03,690 --> 00:01:05,570
and denying that report,

25
00:01:05,570 --> 00:01:09,049
calling it “the worst fake news against
Cambodia.”

26
00:01:09,049 --> 00:01:13,020
Which is yet another lie, because the worst
fake news against Cambodia

27
00:01:13,020 --> 00:01:16,680
is that the prime minister actually “won”
the last election.

28
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:20,660
It’s so much easier to win after you’ve
thrown out all of your opposition.

29
00:01:20,660 --> 00:01:24,009
Also, the naval base thing happens to be true.

30
00:01:24,009 --> 00:01:26,840
Unlike free and fair elections in Cambodia.

31
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:30,329
So what’s the big deal about a Chinese navy
presence in Cambodia?

32
00:01:30,329 --> 00:01:33,950
Well, as I mentioned, that navy base is here.

33
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:36,090
It’s on the Gulf of Thailand.

34
00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:39,649
And that means easy access to the Strait of
Malacca.

35
00:01:39,649 --> 00:01:41,679
And that’s the most important shipping lane

36
00:01:41,679 --> 00:01:44,890
between the Indian Ocean and the Pacific Ocean.

37
00:01:44,890 --> 00:01:47,461
The Pentagon believes it's part of Chinese
regime’s plan

38
00:01:47,461 --> 00:01:52,179
to boost its ability to project military power
around the globe.

39
00:01:52,179 --> 00:01:55,829
And the US is “‘concerned that any steps
by the Cambodian government

40
00:01:55,829 --> 00:01:58,939
to invite a foreign military presence in Cambodia’

41
00:01:58,939 --> 00:02:01,749
would disturb regional peace and stability.”

42
00:02:01,749 --> 00:02:04,899
Although I’m sure if that “foreign military
presence” were the US,

43
00:02:04,899 --> 00:02:07,430
the US might reconsider its concerns.

44
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:10,500
Not that that the Chinese military being there
is really equivalent.

45
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:14,610
Especially considering that the Chinese military
is run by the Communist Party,

46
00:02:14,610 --> 00:02:18,480
which supported the previous Cambodian Khmer
Rouge regime—

47
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:24,390
even as it murdered one quarter of Cambodia’s
population in the 1970s.

48
00:02:24,390 --> 00:02:28,050
Anyway, the base would be Beijing's first
dedicated facility

49
00:02:28,050 --> 00:02:31,220
on the Southeast Asian mainland for naval
staging.

50
00:02:31,220 --> 00:02:32,940
In the navy!

51
00:02:32,940 --> 00:02:36,380
You can sail the seven seas...

52
00:02:36,380 --> 00:02:38,110
In the navy!

53
00:02:38,110 --> 00:02:40,320
That is not naval staging.

54
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:44,150
That is what happens when our graphics guy
spends too much time on YouTube.

55
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:47,390
“Naval staging” is where you put navy
units,

56
00:02:47,390 --> 00:02:50,520
aircraft and warships some place where they
can be prepared

57
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,680
for attacking or invading people.

58
