A former U.S. State Department official says
having a naval base in Cambodia

59
00:02:56,780 --> 00:03:02,110
gives the People’s Liberation Army Navy
a leg up in all of Southeast Asia.

60
00:03:02,110 --> 00:03:05,460
Because “You have all of a sudden mainland
Southeast Asia

61
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:09,740
potentially sitting behind a defensive Chinese
military perimeter.”

62
00:03:09,740 --> 00:03:12,300
And another U.S. official told the Wall Street
Journal

63
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:16,130
that a Chinese presence at Ream would “greatly
complicate”

64
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:21,280
the ability of the U.S. to help Taiwan if
Beijing decides to attack.

65
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:25,420
The Chinese Communist Party opened its first
official military outpost overseas

66
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:28,680
